### Important Note on the use of the arXiv API:

This software utilizes the arXiv API. When using this software, you must adhere to the terms and conditions of the arXiv API:

- E-prints from arXiv are protected by copyright laws. Redistribution of e-prints requires permission from the copyright holder.
- You are free to use descriptive metadata about arXiv e-prints under the terms of the Creative Commons Universal (CC0 1.0) Public Domain Declaration.
- Observe restrictions pertaining to the usage of the arXiv API, including query rate limits.
- Do not attempt to store and serve e-prints (PDFs, source files, etc.) from arXiv unless you have the explicit consent from the copyright holder or are authorized by the license under which the e-print was submitted.

Full terms of use for the arXiv API can be found [here](link to the arXiv API terms of use).
